---
title: "FAQ — Slade Networks"
description: "Answers to common questions about Wi-Fi, cameras, cabling, and network installs for homes and small businesses in the Finger Lakes and surrounding areas in upstate NY."
navActive: faq
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
  <style>
    .section { padding: 12px 0 60px }
    .ctaSection { padding: 0 0 72px }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="heroBadge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
          Common questions answered
        </div>
        <h1>FAQ</h1>
        <p class="subtext">
          Common questions about pricing, how projects work, and what to expect.
        </p>

        <div class="callout">
          <div>
            <h2>Have a question that isn't listed?</h2>
            <p>Email info@sladenetworks.com and we'll reply as soon as possible.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Request a free consultation</a>
            <a class="btn" href="mailto:info@sladenetworks.com?subject=Slade%20Networks%20Question">info@sladenetworks.com</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">Before you start</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                How much does it cost?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Pricing depends on the scope — the size of the space, what's being installed, how much cabling is involved, and what equipment is needed. There's no flat rate because no two projects are the same.
                <br><br>
                As a rough sense: a small home Wi-Fi upgrade is on the lower end. A full install with cabling, cameras, and switching costs more. Equipment and labor are quoted together so there are no surprises.
                <br><br>
                The free consultation is how we get to a real number. After seeing the space and understanding what you want, you'll have a clear quote before any work begins.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do you serve my area?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                We serve the Finger Lakes and surrounding areas in upstate NY — including Penn Yan, Keuka Park, Hammondsport, Watkins Glen, Geneva, Canandaigua, Naples, Victor, and Auburn. If you're outside that range, reach out — travel is sometimes possible depending on the project size.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                What happens during the free consultation?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                We walk through the space, talk through what isn't working and what you want to improve, and put together a simple plan — what equipment is needed, where it goes, and what everything will cost. For Wi-Fi and cameras, we can map the layout to model coverage before anything is installed. You'll have a clear recommendation and quote before any work begins.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do I need to buy equipment before we talk?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                No. Equipment can be sourced as part of the project. If you already have gear on site, we'll look at it and use it where it makes sense.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">The install</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                Can you fix an existing setup, or is this only for new installs?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Both. Some projects are new installs; others are upgrades or fixes — poor Wi-Fi coverage, unreliable cameras, a messy rack. We'll identify what's causing the problem and make a clear plan to fix it.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                How long does a typical project take?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                It depends on the size of the space and what's being installed. Some jobs are a single visit; others take a few days. You'll get a realistic timeline during the consultation before anything starts.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                What equipment do you use?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Most installs use UniFi by Ubiquiti. It brings Wi-Fi, cameras, switching, and phone systems into a single dashboard — fewer apps to manage, one consistent system, and simpler support over time. It's proven hardware that's designed to be updated and maintained for years.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">After the install</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                Will I keep full access to my own system?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Yes. You get admin access and a full walkthrough at handoff. Nothing is locked away or hidden.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do I have to sign up for ongoing support?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                No. Most projects are one-time installs with a clean handoff. Ongoing remote administration is available for clients who want monitoring, proactive updates, and faster troubleshooting — but it's entirely optional.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                How do I get help after the job is done?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Email <a href="mailto:support@sladenetworks.com">support@sladenetworks.com</a>. If remote support is set up on your system, many issues can be handled quickly without a site visit.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ctaSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ctaInner">
          <div>
            <h2>Ready to move forward?</h2>
            <p>Book a free consultation and we'll put together a plan for your space — no commitment required.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Request a free consultation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
{% endblock %}
